<plot>Holly applies color theory to her artwork and film theory to her social life. By asking men their favorite film, she can tell whether they are date-worthy or not. The weeding out process works so well, Holly finds herself without any prospective suitors. Desperate for love since breaking up with her longtime beau, Holly pushes logic aside and makes a birthday wish for a new leading man in her life. Yet when the smoke clears, she mistakenly sets her sights on a scrap-eating busboy. To steer Holly away from a dating disaster (and to put her own mind at ease) Holly's friend Pam urges her to pursue other prospects. Hastily, Holly looks past an attentive bartender as she asks three bachelors their favorite film. When their answers fall short, it just confirms her hunch that the busboy must be "the one." To be certain of this, Holly must test her film theory one last time. Would you risk your chance at romance by asking the man of your dreams, "what is your favorite film?" Holly would.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?243073</url></doc>
